"""
================================================================================
  ChemMotion v2 - Sketch & Motion Studio with Chemistry Templates
  A 2D animation tool for chemistry video creators.

  FEATURES:
  - Draw: Pen, Line, Arrow, Circle, Filled Dot, Rectangle, Text
  - Move: Keyframe-based motion with smooth tweening
  - Orbit: Auto-generate circular orbit keyframes (electrons!)
  - Fade:  Fade objects in/out with opacity keyframes
  - Templates: One-click atoms, electrons, bonds, arrows, orbitals
  - Export: Animated GIF at 960x540 (16:9)

  HOW TO RUN:
      pip install pillow
      python chem_motion_v2.py

  QUICK WORKFLOW:
  1. Use the Templates panel (left) to stamp atoms & electrons onto the canvas.
  2. Switch to SELECT tool. Drag the timeline to a later frame.
  3. Drag objects to animate them (keyframes are auto-set).
  4. Use "Add Orbit" to make electrons orbit a nucleus.
  5. Use "Fade In / Fade Out" to make bonds or labels appear/disappear.
  6. Press PLAY to preview. Click EXPORT GIF when happy.
================================================================================
"""

